  "text": "A few of the underlying genetic causes for this variation have been shown to affect elements of both innate and adaptive immunity. Recent work has now established solid evidence for two hypotheses long suspected but as yet with little empirical evidence: first, that there are intermediate levels of immune response that are optimal, and second, that some genetic differences confer advantages against a broad range of infectious agents [CITATION_1] .",
